{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"23":"Commercial Transactions (Kitab Al-Buyu)"},"section_detail":{"23":{"hadithnumber_first":3326,"hadithnumber_last":3415,"arabicnumber_first":3326,"arabicnumber_last":3415}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3373,"arabicnumber":3373,"text":"Rapporté par Jabir ibn Abdullah : Le Prophète ﷺ a interdit la vente de fruits tant qu’ils ne sont pas manifestement en bon état, et (a ordonné) qu’ils ne soient vendus que contre dinar ou dirham, sauf pour les ‘araya","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Bukhari (2381) Sahih Muslim (1536 After 1543)"}],"reference":{"book":23,"hadith":48}}]}